SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CENTER IS A NONPROFIT CORPORATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) AND, THEREFORE, HAS MADE NO PROVISION FOR FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES IN THE ACCOMPANYING CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. IN ADDITION, THE CENTER QUALIFIES FOR THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DECUCTION UNDER SECTION 170(B)(1)(A)VI AND HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER SECTION 509(A)(2). THE CENTER HAS ANALYZED ITS TAX POSITIONS TAKEN FOR FILINGS WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. IT BELIEVES THAT ITS TAX FILING POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION AND DOES NOT ANTICIPATE ANY ADJUSTMENTS THAT WOULD RESULT IN A MATERIAL ADVERSE EFFECT ON THE FINANCIAL CONDITION, RESULTS OF OPERATIONS, OR CASH FLOWS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE IS NO COMMITTEE WITH AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION CONTROLLER REVIEWS THE 990 WITH THE CHIEF OPERATING OFFICER AND, FOLLOWING ANY NEEDED CORRECTIONS FROM THAT REVIEW, THEN FORWARDS THE 990 TO THE PRESIDENT OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR FINAL APPROVAL AND SIGNATURE. THE 990 IS AVAILABLE TO THE CEO AND OTHER BOARD MEMBERS WHEN REQUESTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY COVERS ALL BOARD MEMBERS, OFFICERS OF THE ORGANIZATION AND OTHER KEY LEADERSHIP STAFF. THE INTERESTED PERSON DISCLOSES THE EXISTENCE AND THE MATERIAL FACTS REGARDING A POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST TO THE BOARD; THE BOARD WILL DETERMINE IF CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS. THE INTERESTED PERSON MAY NOT BE PRESENT IN THE BOARD MEETING AND MAY NOT VOTE ON THE TRANSACTION. THE BOARD WILL DETERMINE ANY APPROPRIATE DISCIPLINARY OR CORRECTIVE ACTION. ALL PROCEEDINGS RELATED TO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ARE DOCUMENTED IN THE MEETING MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RURAL HEALTH RESOURCE CENTER (CENTER) WILL PERIODICALLY, GENERALLY EVERY THREE YEARS, UTILIZE A COMPENSATION CONSULTING FIRM TO PROVIDE A COMPETITIVE MARKET REVIEW FOR THE CEO, COO, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND ALL OTHER STAFF, COMPARING CURRENT PAY LEVELS TO THE MARKET PAY. ANNUALLY IN THE INTERIM YEARS, THE COMPENSATION CONSULTING FIRM WILL PROVIDE MARKET SURVEY DATA TO PROVIDE LABOR MARKET RATE ADJUSTMENTS. THE CENTER PRESENTS ALL COMPENSATION RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE FOR REVIEW AND APPROVAL. THIS PROCESS WAS LAST DONE IN 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO INTERESTED THIRD PARTIES. FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE ALSO AVAILABLE WITH THE STATE OF MN ATTORNEY GENERAL.
